<li id="cite_note-46"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-46">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Dina_Thanthi" title="Dina Thanthi">Dina Thanthi</a> (Tamil Daily), <i><a href="Nagercoil" title="Nagercoil">Nagercoil</a> Edition</i>, 4 March 2007, Page 23: <i>"The Ayyavazhi followers are highly populated in the districts of <a href="Chennai" title="Chennai">Chennai</a>, <a href="Virudunagar" title="Virudunagar" class="mw-redirect">Virudunagar</a>, <a href="Tirunelveli" title="Tirunelveli">Tirunelveli</a>, <a href="Tuticorin" title="Tuticorin" class="mw-redirect">Tuticorin</a> and <a href="Kanyakumari_district" title="Kanyakumari district">Kanyakumari</a>."</i></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-47"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-47">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Tha. Krishna Nathan's, Ayyaa vaikundarin vaazvum sinthanaiyum (Tamil), (Thesis in <a href="Madurai_Kamaraj_University" title="Madurai Kamaraj University">Madurai Kamaraj University</a>), <i>Thinai Veliyeettagam</i>, Chapter – 4, page 83.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Menachery-48"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Menachery_48-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Menachery G (1973) The St. Thomas Christian Encyclopedia of India, Ed. George Menachery, B.N.K. Press, vol. 2, <a href="Special_BookSources/818713206X" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 81-87132-06-X</a>, Lib. Cong. Cat. Card. No. 73-905568; B.N.K. Press – (has some 70 lengthy articles by different experts on the origins, development, history, culture... of these Christians, with some 300 odd photographs).</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Menachery1-49"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Menachery1_49-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Menachery G (ed) (1982) The St. Thomas Christian Encyclopedia of India, B.N.K. Press, vol. 1;</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Menachery2-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Menachery2_50-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Menachery G (ed); (1998) "The Indian Church History Classics", Vol. I, The Nazranies, Ollur, 1998. [<a href="Special_BookSources/8187133058" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 81-87133-05-8</a>].</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Mundalan-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Mundalan_51-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Mundadan, A. Mathias. (1984) History of Christianity in India, vol.1, Bangalore, India: Church History Association of India.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Podipara-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Podipara_52-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Podipara, Placid J. (1970) "The Thomas Christians". London: Darton, Longman and Tidd, 1970. (is a readable and exhaustive study of the St. Thomas Christians.)</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Lbrown-53"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Lbrown_53-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Leslie Brown, (1956) The Indian Christians of St. Thomas. An Account of the Ancient Syrian Church of Malabar, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press 1956, 1982 (repr.)</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Puthiakunnel-54"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Puthiakunnel_54-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Puthiakunnel_54-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Thomas Puthiakunnel, (1973) "Jewish colonies of India paved the way for St. Thomas", The Saint Thomas Christian Encyclopedia of India, ed. George Menachery, Vol. II., Trichur.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Koder-55"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Koder_55-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Koder S. 'History of the Jews of Kerala".The St. Thomas Christian Encyclopaedia of India, Ed. G. Menachery,1973.</span></li>
